The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Manan not allowed to board flight
                                                                                                                       7                                      Manan not allowed to board flight
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: All-rounder Manan Sharma, a member of the Indian under-19 team who were on their way back from New Zealand Friday, was not allowed to board his flight back home from New Zealand because his hand injury was not properly dressed.         
	Manan Sharma, a member of the Indian under-19 team that was on its way back from New Zealand earlier today, was not allowed to board flight SQ 298 CHC  SIN. The airline refused to let him travel with his teammates as his hand injury had not been dressed properly, BCCI secretary N. Srinivasan said in a statement.         
	He will be returning on Saturday.                                                                                                                     
